abstract: A single-payer system can lower prices by setting them. But lots of countries regulate prices and have private insurance, too.
snippet: A single-payer system can lower prices by setting them. But lots of countries regulate prices and have private insurance, too.
lead_paragraph: One way Elizabeth Warren wants to control health care spending in the United States is simple in principle: Pay doctors and hospitals significantly less.

headline_main: Warren Has Her Plan. Buttigieg Suggests Another Way to Cut Health Prices.
headline_print_headline: Warren’s Plan Targets Insurers. Buttigieg Aims at Hospitals.

abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. unfurled sharply personal new lines of attack against Senator Elizabeth Warren on Tuesday, questioning her contributions to the Democratic Party and seeking to cast her as an elitist who believes people lack courage or wisdom unless they agree with her.

abstract: President Trump’s decision to quit the Paris climate accord met with harsh words from the Democratic presidential candidates.
snippet: President Trump’s decision to quit the Paris climate accord met with harsh words from the Democratic presidential candidates.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s decision on Monday to begin the formal process of withdrawing from the Paris climate agreement prompted outrage from the Democratic presidential candidates, who may try to use the existential threat of climate change to motivate voters.

abstract: Why can’t financial tycoons handle criticism?
snippet: Why can’t financial tycoons handle criticism?
lead_paragraph: Given all the recent focus on health policy, you might think that the medical-industrial complex would be heavily involved in the Democratic primary race, going all-out to block Elizabeth Warren. And a coalition of drug companies, insurers and hospitals is indeed running ads attacking “Medicare for all.”

abstract: National polls have him firmly behind the leading candidates across the country, and questions remain over Mr. Buttigieg’s ability to create a diverse coalition. But in Iowa, he’s on the rise.
snippet: National polls have him firmly behind the leading candidates across the country, and questions remain over Mr. Buttigieg’s ability to create a diverse coalition. But in Iowa, he’s on the rise.
lead_paragraph: DECORAH, Iowa — Ask almost any Iowa Democrat, and they’ll tell you: Pete Buttigieg is smart.

lead_paragraph: “We are so outside of our comfort zones,”  Helen Mirren was saying as she sat with Ian McKellen onstage at the Booth Theater  on Sunday night.

abstract: And without reform, neither is a Democratic Senate.
snippet: And without reform, neither is a Democratic Senate.
lead_paragraph: There are still more than a dozen candidates jockeying for the Democratic presidential nomination. Some are running on big, ambitious platforms for change, like the Medicare-for-All plans pushed by Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren. Others are selling “pragmatism,” with more modest ideas meant to win consensus — and which are often quite liberal by historical standards. But nearly everyone on the board faces the same, fundamental problem: They want to go further than where Congress, and the Senate in particular, will want to move, even if it has a Democratic majority.

lead_paragraph: A progressive organization is plunging itself into the presidential campaign, unveiling plans to spend $75 million on digital advertising to counter President Trump’s early spending advantage in key 2020 battleground states.
